nodes.bodyText:
This is correct, it just doesn't need to be this long and isn't instantly recognisable as double checked locking.
  private WeakCache<ClassLoader, Boolean> getCache() {
     if (cacheHolder == null) {
         synchronized (this) {
             if (cacheHolder == null) {
                 cacheHolder = AgentTooling.newWeakCache(25);
             }
         }
     }
     return cacheHolder;
    }
Is shorter and more idiomatic. The first thing someone will do when they read that code is check if cacheHolder is volatile and then carry on.

